	<div class='panel nonFeedback'>
		<h3 title='Why Lease Instruments?'><a href='#'></a></h3>
		<div class='panelContent nonFeedback'>
			<p>
				When you obtain a bank instrument at a discounted percentage, below the actual face value, it is called a
				Leased Instrument. Rather than reselling the Leased Instrument for a yield-spread profit, the instrument is
				leased by the investor, at a rate of well below the face value. This is repeated continuously and within a
				short period, the original cost is recovered and profits are realized from the Instrument.
			</p>
			<p>
				Leased Instruments are utilized for various reasons like Credit Enhancement, Trade Programs, and
				Collateralization for a Loan or to have the Instrument Monetized to Cash for a myriad of projects. It is
				good that you found us because we lease instruments at a competitive price and can provide, deliver and
				offer programs that are of value for your projects.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class='panel nonFeedback'>
		<h3 title='Leasing Procedures'><a href='#'></a></h3>
		<div class='panelContent nonFeedback'>
			<p>Our standard, and <em>preferred</em> method of transacting business is to use a third-party
			escrow escrow using a license and bonded attorney for both yours and our protection.
			<span class='Highlight'>We will now lease using escrow (preferred) or MT103/23 procedures.</span> However, even if we do a MT103/23 we will still require $100,000 to be put into escrow to cover sending a MT-760.</p>
			<ol>
				<li><span class='normal'>
					Complete a <a href='./CISform.doc'>Client Information Sheet</a>
					and submit it along with the listed documents.</span></li>
				<li><span class='normal'>A service agreement outlining the contractual term is issued.</span></li>
				<li><span class='normal'>Sign and return the service and escrow agreement.</span></li>
				<li><span class='normal'>Wire escrow lease fees to the third-party escrow company.</span></li>
				<li><span class='normal'>The instrument is sent by SWIFT to your nominated bank.</span></li>
				<li><span class='normal'>Once instrument is received and verified by your bank, instruct escrow agent to release the fees from escrow.</span></li>
			</ol>
